tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows mildly elevated HbA1c, indicating impaired glucose regulation or possible early diabetes, despite a low fasting glucose level. Renal function, electrolytes, and other parameters are within normal limits. Recommend further evaluation for glucose metabolism (e.g., repeat fasting glucose, oral glucose tolerance test) and clinical correlation for possible hypoglycemic episodes.
